Implemented zoom gestures + distance range control for Over the Horizon iOS AR app.

CHANGES:
1. Created ZoomGestureManager.swift - Manages pinch zoom state, distance ranges, and label scaling
   - Pinch OUT: increases min/max distances, smaller labels (zoom out view)
   - Pinch IN: decreases min/max distances, larger labels (focus nearer)
   - Zoom level range: 0.3x (max zoom in) to 3.0x (max zoom out)
   - Labels disappear when closer than min distance (dynamically set by zoom)

2. Modified ARLabelPositioner.swift - Now supports dynamic distance ranges and label scaling
   - Accepts minDistance, maxDistance, and labelScaleMultiplier parameters
   - Font sizes scaled by labelScaleMultiplier (inverse of zoom level)
   - Still respects reasonable min/max bounds

3. Updated ContentView.swift
   - Added @StateObject for ZoomGestureManager
   - Integrated MagnificationGesture to capture pinch zoom input
   - Display zoom level info in debug HUD (zoom level + distance range)
   - Pass zoom manager to AROverlayView

4. Updated AROverlayView.swift
   - Accepts ZoomGestureManager as @ObservedObject
   - Creates ARLabelPositioner with dynamic zoom values
   - Labels update position, size, and visibility based on zoom

5. Comprehensive test coverage (40+ new tests)
   - ZoomGestureManager: initialization, zoom bounds, gesture handling, distance/label updates
   - ARLabelPositioner integration: font sizing with zoom, display filtering
   - Integration tests: full zoom workflows, smooth transitions, gesture chains

TESTING:
- All existing tests remain passing
- 40 new tests covering zoom functionality (ZoomGestureManagerTests, ARLabelPositionerWithZoomTests, ZoomAROverlayIntegrationTests)
- Tests verify: bounds checking, smooth responses, distance range control, label scaling
- Swift syntax validation: all files parse without errors

BEHAVIOR:
✓ Smooth pinch response - zoom level updates continuously during gesture
✓ Reasonable min/max bounds - absolute bounds prevent extreme values
✓ Labels scale dynamically - inverse relationship to zoom (zoom out = smaller labels)
✓ Distance visibility changes - zoom in shows closer POIs, zoom out shows farther POIs
✓ Does NOT change camera FOV - only adjusts distance thresholds and label sizes
